comment.author: 41909278@N08
comment._content:
Two features which always went hand in hand can be seen on this AT-6F. First of all the Harvard style rear canopy (no frames on AT-6 aircraft) and the rectangular baggage door, immediately above the mechanic's head. NA-16 family members that had the triangular 'flip over' rear canopies always had a five sided baggage door.

Doug MacPhail
